cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.CL, cs.GR 

This paper proposes an unsupervised learning approach for feature learning from point cloud data using graph neural networks. The approach involves contrasting and clustering of the data, which are common techniques used in computer vision (cs.CV) and machine learning (cs.LG, cs.AI). The use of graph neural networks also suggests a potential fit for the graphics (cs.GR) category. Additionally, the paper evaluates the proposed approach on point cloud classification tasks, which could also place it in the natural language processing (cs.CL) category.
